lowshade Moor War</span><hr size=1> As some of you may know I've been obsessing over the Vah Shir racial quest &quot;The Hero of Shar Vahl.&quot;  This is a huge quest that I seriously doubt I will ever complete because the final stages require very large groups and the completion of the Grimling Forest wars.  Unlike the &quot;General's Challenge&quot; method of completing the wars, the Vah Shir racial quest gives you a nice crafing skill boosting cloak that increases in power as you do the quest.<br>
<br>
Anyway, I've been grouping pretty often lately with a Bard kitty named Jillaroo.  We go around and mass murder mobs in Hollowshade Moor for quest drops we need for the crafting part of the quest.  This is the Sonic Wolfbane Quest that you might hear Vah Shir players moaning about every once in a while.  It's really hard.<br>
<br>
For Sonic Wolfbane, you need to get five crafted components, each by a Shar Vahl citizen of appropriate class.  Very few people get this far, just because its a pain (lots of rare drop camping), so its hard to find all of the people.  I can craft the beastlord part, and Jillaroo can make the bard and shaman parts, so we've been trying to get all the drops we need to make all of those parts.<br>
<br>
Last night, we grouped with a beastlord name Recoil.  His rogue has been working on the rogue part of the quest, so we were clear cutting sonic wolves.<br>
<br>
Alright, here is a brief diversion.  Hollowshade Moor is a big zone next to Shar Vahl and Grimling Forest.  There are three factions in the zone: Sonic Wolves, Owlbears, and Grimlings.  Each side has territory and each side tries to invade the other side.  If players are killing one side a lot, one of the other sides will try to attack that side.  When this happens, a set of guardians spawn in front of the &quot;castle&quot; for that side.  The attackers send a green attack force that can't possibly kill the guardians.  BUT, if you get involved and take out the guardians, the attackers win.  That causes the defending faction to despawn out of that area and the winning faction to take over and repop in that whole area.<br>
<br>
When one side controls the whole Moor, they spawn a huge army and attack the nearby Vah Shir outpost.  They always win if they get this far.  This causes that faction to control the entire zone and the &quot;king&quot; for that faction spawns.  The king is tough and has great equipment drops.  His corpse decays 30 seconds after you kill him so you have to loot fast.  Then the zone resets.<br>
<br>
Anyway, last night we got the owlbears to take over the whole zone.  There is a bug that caused the king not to spawn, though.  A big disappointment.<br>
<br>
That aside, I picked up some neat loot.  <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.geocities.com/hollowshademoor/HollowshadeMain.html" target="top">This link</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> describes some of the possible permutations for the war and the drops.  If you guys haven't heard of the war, you should poke around the site and look at some of the drops.  They aren't too hard to get and some are quite nice.<br>
<br>
Until I can get my part crafted and enough parts crafted for my friends and they get parts crafted for me, I'll probably be in HM off and on from time to time.  If you are looking for a particular drop, let me know and maybe we can rig the war to go a certain way.<br>
<br>
It can be a hassle of a zone, but its also very fun to play with.  It's neat to see one faction take over an area of the game completely, just because you interfered with their war.<br>
<br>
Big thanks to the guildmates who were on tonight giving me encouragement.  I don't think many of them knew much about the War, but they were cheering each time I announced something happened.<br>
<br>
That really made the whole evening quite enjoyable, even though we didn't get Skrietat Chakku to spawn. <p>--<br>
